26th January, 2006

When using the persistant death system when a player logs in, after a server reset, his death corpse will appear at the GraveYard marker.
It's recommeneded you place the GraveYard marker in a temple along with the BagYard marker.

The GodLoc Marker is used if the God System is in use.
If the player has a valid deity and are saved at the time of death they will appear at the GodLoc marker.
It's recommended you place this in your temple also.
The default chance that a player will be raised by their god if they have one by  is 5% +1% per 4 levels of the character.

HCR Newbie Store - Move to your start location with the merchant waypoint.

HCR Signpost is found at Placeables > Custom > Pennant's & Signs > HCR Signpost.

Store is found at Paint Merchants > Custom > Special > Custom 1 place this near the HCR Signpost.
This is a skinning knife.  It is not very useful in combat but when used on a corpse can produce hide and meat.  Rangers also use it to hunt.
This tool can be used to pick locks or  disarm traps.
This tool can be used to pick locks or  disarm traps.
This is a standard lantern, you must refill it with oil every 6 hours of use.

An oil-soaked rag plugs the mouth of this bottle.

This is a grenade-like weapon. Target it at your enemies and beware of splash damage.
This is a standard cheap disposable torch.
This is a bedroll.  You can use it by placing it on the ground.
This is a bedroll, to use it, drop it on the ground.

This is a water canteen. No adventurer should be without one.

Target a source of water to fill the canteen, or target the ground near you while you are standing next to water.
These curative potions are too expensive for most civilians, and are used almost exclusively by soldiers and adventurers.

Consisting of Flint and Steel this box can start 25 fires before the flint wears out.

Use this item on the ground to create campfires. If you want to extend thier burning time use a oilflask on the campfire.
The kit is full of herbs, salves, bandages, and other useful material.  It may be used to stop bleeding, cure poison or disease, and increase the recovery rate of resting patients.
